Taxonomy of this genus has been in flux for some time, and prior to 2007, only one species (S. 
fluviatilis
) and two subspecies, a riverine type (
fluviatilis
) and a coastal type (
guianensis
), were recognized. An accumulation of genetic evidence, in addition to ecological and morphological differences, supports separate species status for these two types. Monotypic.
